Adversarial review:
  Cycle 1 (review-1.json): verdict fix-blockers — flagged the
    millisecond-collision data loss. Boundary drop was too aggressive.
  Cycle 2 (review-2.json): verdict ship — 0 blockers; 2 nits (boundary
    id-set growth under pathological same-ms storms; EVENTS_PAGE_CAP
    silent truncation).

Notes / decisions:
  - Single-events expansion + show_deleted + order_by=updated is the
    minimum-friction shape for Google Calendar list queries that
    advance reliably on update time. show_deleted lets the high-water
    advance past cancellations rather than getting stuck behind them.
  - Initial fix attempt was rejected by the reviewer as a real
    correctness bug (not a style nit) — addressed via id-aware
    boundary handling + state extension. Reviewer's flag was a
    high-value catch.
  - last_seen_event_ids growth is bounded in normal operation
    (single ms collisions are rare; any later event resets the
    set). Unbounded only under pathological "many events at the
    same ms forever" — not a real workload.

